A RESOLUTION
To express the condolences of the House of Representatives upon the death of William
"Billy" Henry D'Aquilla.
WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing, on April 12,
2026, of William "Billy" Henry D'Aquilla; and
WHEREAS, Billy was born on September 8, 1940, in Fort Adams, Mississippi, to
Frank and Velma Stutzmann D'Aquilla; and
WHEREAS, though Billy was born in Mississippi, he dedicated his life to the people
of St. Francisville, Louisiana; he was elected as town alderman and mayor pro tempore in
1972, and he was elected mayor in 1984; and
WHEREAS, Billy proudly and humbly presided over St. Francisville's town
government until his retirement in 2020; he served nearly five decades with unwavering
dedication and guided the town through seasons of growth, challenge, and celebration; and
WHEREAS, Billy was known for his open-door policy, humor, and tireless
advocacy, and he truly valued every voice in the community; he was also the sole proprietor
of a popular local grocery store for many years, and he went on to work as a sales associate
for National American Wholesale; and
WHEREAS, Billy's life was a testament to the power of service, compassion, and
hometown pride; and
